profile:
Quality Potlight is a family owned and operated business that specializes in top quality CANADIAN APPROVED pot lights. Since our inception in 2009, Quality Pot lights has serviced well over 5,000 homes, offices and condos throughout Greater Toronto Area including: Downtown Toronto, Forest Hill, Rosedale, Yorkville, Royal York, Scarborough, East York, North York, Etobicoke, Mississauga, Oakville, Burlington, Vaughan, Brampton, Thornhill, Markham, Richmond Hill, Aurora, Stouffville, Pickering, Ajax & Newmarket. Our consistent level of high-quality work and dedication to ensuring that the needs of every client are met have allowed us to quickly grow into a leader in quality potlight installation. We understand that your home is the largest investment you will ever make and are willing to go above and beyond perfection to ensure that you are satisfied.

ESA#: 7010623

Please visit www.qualitypotlight.ca

Been in business since 2009, Quality Potlight has the expertise and skills to accomplish a wide range of projects in your home. Our trained staff are exceptionally pleasant to deal with and are diligent in ensuring that that there is absolutely no mess or damage from our installation. 

At Quality Potlight we believe that the best way to build relationships is through integrity, performance, value, and client satisfaction. We strive to be a prominent provider of superior electrical services by constantly keeping our inventory updated with the latest innovative products as well as constantly focusing on improving the speed and service of our staff. All electrical works are done by our ESA certified and insured contractors who specialize in Pot light installation.

We are committed to providing an excellent service across Toronto, GTA and nearby regions. In our decade of experience, we have learned that you can get your appliance, HVAC, electrical and plumbing issues repaired quickly, effectively, and relatively inexpensively. Our specialty is to provide quick solutions to all your appliance, plumbing, HVAC and electrical repairs and to achieve the highest possible customer satisfaction from our services. Our punctual and friendly staff will always provide budget-friendly repairs.

WHY DO OUR CUSTOMERS LOVE US?
"Slow is smooth, smooth is fast." This is our motto because we take exceptional care in locating your appliance and plumbing faults to have them fixed within the shortest possible period. We encourage our customers to watch us as we perform the repair and to ask as many questions as possible while we are on site. This will ensure the best service on the market because you will be educated on all of your appliances at no extra cost.
Man With a Wrench always provides an above and beyond service because we do not simply tackle the problem at hand. We also find its underlying cause. Most importantly, we provide our customers with education as to how to prevent such problems from occurring in the future. Our budget-friendly repairs are second to none and we will provide you with quick solutions to all of your appliance repair needs. Our goal is to delight you with our service. profile:
Heating & Air Conditioning

COOLING
At Belyea Bros. we install and service a range of air conditioning systems including forced air (central) air conditioning, ductless split air conditioners, and our custom designed Attic Pak and SpacePak systems. Due to our background as a hot water heating specialists we are experts at planning and executing cooling solutions for houses without ductwork.

HEATING
At Belyea Bros. Limited we hold the first heating license issued in Toronto. As a result, we have the experience to claim, “there is nothing about heating we don’t know”. We are experts in hot water, radiant in-floor, snow melt systems and forced air heating. Over a number of years we have carefully selected the products that we recommend to our customers. We sell only manufacturers that have a proven track record of quality and service so that we can offer you the best support possible. All the manufacturers we work with have parts centers or distributors within the GTA meaning we have access to a local support network. We offer only reliable premium equipment.

HOT WATER TANKS 
Water heater rentals are a great solution for many homeowners who have a short-to-medium time frame in their house, own a tenanted property, are looking for a peace-of-mind solution to address their domestic hot water needs, or simply wish to have a clear idea of their monthly house budget over the long term without the worry of heater repairs.

Many consumers are confused by which company they actually rent their water heater from, thinking that because the charge appears on their gas bill that they rent from “gas-company”. In fact, most customers in Toronto rent their heaters from Centrica PLC, an international energy services company based in the United Kingdom, which operates in Canada under the brand name Direct Energy™. Although they bill on the gas bill, they are not, in any way, affiliated with your gas utility.

Belyea Bros. has a wide range of hot water tank solutions for your family’s needs. We have an excellent rental program providing a comparable rate and great reliable products. We provide a fix rate increase, unlike the other guys who may raise your billing at anytime. 

TANKLESS HOT WATER
Tankless hot water heaters are common in Europe and Japan. They can supply an endless supply of hot water, with greater energy savings than conventional tanks. They are, however, limited in the amount of hot water that can be produced at one time and the upfront costs are higher.

ELECTRICAL SERVICE
Belyea Bros. Electrical specializes in helping home and business owners in the older neighborhoods of Toronto. We provide electrical service, repair and installation whether it’s diagnosing and fixing a broken outlet, or re-wiring your whole home, Belyea Bros. Electrical is here to help.

We service work form $400.00 to $500,000.00+ from our Painter and Handyman of the Day Service to  Home Additions and Major Renovation and Structural work.   We want to earn your trust and as a family owned business that delivers on providing outstanding home/office renovation work. 

Not convinced we have enough renovation reviews please see Perfect Painters & Home Renovations Services for a more detailed list on reviews.

We have a commitment to Quality work and dealing with a no risk contractor and we will always compete for your business.


We have also expanded our service areas to include Burlington, Oakville, Milton, Mississauga, Brampton, Toronto, Vaughan, Markham, Newmark, Aurora, Stouffville, Pickering and Oshawa.

Call or email us at sales@thig.pro for all your renovation needs

profile:
Sandu Electric is a family run business with over 15 years of experience in the trade. We are equipped to handle all of your residential & commercial needs.



Sandu Electric has been a full service, third generation, family-owned and operated company since 1996. We provide electrical services to Toronto and surrounding areas with a focus on commercial, industrial, institutional, and residential designs.
We have successfully completed every project awarded to us in a timely manner, along with the highest quality workmanship. We can handle any size project and installation from initial design to follow-up maintenance.


Sandu Electric is a fully licensed company with up to five million in liability insurance for our customers' protection. We are a pre-authorized electrical contractor with ESA (Electrical Safety Authority).



Sandu Electric is fully licensed and insured to protect you, the Home Owner. Our high quality workmanship allows us to guarantee against workmanship defects for one year and we honor all manufactures warranties.

profile:
Vision
We Started Safe Electrical Solutions is an electrical contractor service under ESA (Electrical Safety Authority) License No. 7010337. Our vision is “to make your living and work place electrically safe and reduce the potential risk to your property”. We are committed to deliver optimistic and safe electrical solutions for our every client.
5 Star Service
We specifically address residential and commercial electrical services and repairs. Because we believe “Our Clients Deserve Five Star Service”. We work hard and put every effort to deliver highest quality of electrical service to our clients.  If you face any electrical problem or decided to upgrade the electrical system in home, office and kind of residential and work places, we are capable to deliver the safest and fast electrical repairs and upgrade. 
Experience and Technology change
In our electrical contractor business, all of our electricians are licensed and exceptionally skilled for residential and commercial electrical services. Mainstream of our electricians carrying over 20 years of experience. We keep our electrician and technicians into continuous learning process and update their knowledge. So any technology change and electrical code change does not give us any hesitation to deliver same quality of service and provide you safe electrical solutions.
Provide and Install
We are affiliated with all major Home improvement stores from where you go to buy any electrical device or appliances. This way we know which kind of device or appliance, you want to have. We provide and install exactly the same product in a safest way and ensure your satisfaction.
Neighbourhood with fully equipped truck
Our electricians network is spread all over GTA (Greater Toronto Area) with fully equipped trucks carrying all standard material, might needed when our electrician is at your premises to work for you to fix your electrical problem. Just consider we are in your neighbourhood.  
So does not matter, if you call from us Toronto downtown, east or west, Scarborough to Vaughn, York region, all of Peel Region specially Mississauga, Brampton, and relevant areas, our scheduled time window, work price and quality of work remains same. 
24/7 emergency service 
With a commitment to make your life and premises safe, we provide 24/7 service even during, all weekends and public holidays. Our troubleshooting specialists’ remains standby with fully equipped trucks to provide service and keep you even more satisfied. If you face any electrical trouble in the night, day, weekend or holiday, feel free to call us.

Volt Master Inc. is an Ontario based electrical company specializing in residential, commercial and industrial electrical installations and service work. Our quality workmanship has earned us a reputation as one of the province's premiere electrical contractors. We specialize in ground-up construction as well as renovations, add-ons, and remodeling and retro fitting. We are experts in providing on sites solutions.

Our projects have a 96% on time completion record with less than 1% deficiency ratio.

Distinctive Homes

We will design and build your electrical system to function the way you want. Period. No surprises or disappointments. If you can dream it, we can build it. We maintain control throughout the design and construction process to ensure that the electrical distribution system in your residence is built to the highest quality standards.

Commercial and Industrial

We manage all stages of your project. From the pre-design phase of a project through construction and delivery. We form alliances with property owners, architects, structural engineers, and specialized trades people. We are proud holders of a Master's Electrical Contractors license.

Volt Master Inc:

On schedule completion
Cost-effective process from beginning to end

Honesty, integrity, and great value

Expert GTA Electric Inc  provides high-quality, price effective solutions for your home or business and our area of work is new construction, repair, maintenance and service.

We work on projects ranging from small residential installations to large scale commercial and industrial projects.
Expert GTA Electric Inc is the most trusted and effective Electrical Contractor to provide the most reliable, timely and cost-effective electrical services to our Residential, Commercial and Industrial clients.

We provide electrical services in the GTA area. Please Feel free to contact us for any Commercial, Industrial or Residential Electrical Services in the GTA area.
Contact us at 647 409 1488 for a free Electrical Service quote for any residential, commercial or industrial projects. 24-hour emergency services are available .


MAIN RESIDENTIAL SERVICES
Electrical Panel Upgrade
An electrical panel upgrade may be required due to renovation or because your current panel can no longer securely handle your home’s demands. You should know that only a licensed electrician can perform a panel upgrade. Your electrical panel is a vital component of your home and should be well maintained and highly functional. As your electrical needs evolve, you may need to modify your electrical panel to avoid safety difficulties and fire hazards. Additionally, all maintenance on your electrical panel should be performed by a certified electrician.

Electrical Wiring & Rewiring
There are a plethora of reasons why you might require wire installations in a new area of your house. If you need to wire light fixtures, track lighting, ceiling fans, new outlets, switches, electrical panels, sound systems, security cameras, or anything else our electrical team can help. Our electricians have worked on both Commercial and Residential wiring projects; this guarantees that we will be able to perform any electrical repair or installation required to make your property safe.

MAIN COMMERCIAL SERVICES
Electrical Repair & Trouble Shooting
Electrical issues can occur at any time. Our skilled and experienced professionals are available to respond swiftly to your electrical needs 7 days a week. Our electricians want to help you create the property of your dreams.

Lighting Systems
Having up-to-date lighting systems is energy efficient and beneficial for the environment. It allows you to fully harness the power your pre-existing electrical system offers with much higher reliability and lower maintenance.

MAIN INDUSTRIAL SERVICES
Industrial Process Improvement
Expert GTA Electric is a Toronto-based industrial electrical company committed to meeting all of your industrial electrical requirements while also delivering expert execution of electrical design-build solutions for your company.

In addition to installations and designs, our electricians also work on electrical repairs and upgrades as well as maintenance and troubleshooting. If you want to enhance energy efficiency while also increasing productivity and reducing downtime, we are the solution for you.

Industrial services include anything from lighting retrofits and solutions to Programmable Logic Control & Control Panel Design, as well as the installation of signs and panels, or power and distribution equipment installation.

Installation of lights and smoke detectors
Expert GTA Electric is the electrical business to call when you need the installation of fire protective/preventive devices. All workplaces are required to have a smoke detection system by law. Hardwired smoke detectors are the most effective method of protecting those we care about. Expert GTA Electric can install and change the smoke detector system in your company, ensuring that you are protected at all times. Our experts will carry out a thorough investigation to personalize our services to your specific needs.

Expert GTA Electric can also assist you to save money on energy costs. We recommend that our clients switch to LED retrofit lighting. This can save electricity use by up to 70 percent while also lasting 25 times longer than incandescent bulbs. This installation should be completed by a certified electrician.

profile:
Choosing the right contractor is similar to choosing a dentist, doctor, or any specialized profession - make a mistake in your choice and it may cost you dearly. There are a number of ways to qualify a contractor and make sure you have the right professional for the right job. Electricians are very skilled tradesman that go through a rigorous training process involving formal education, apprenticeship, and licensing. Every electrician should be licensed and insured in your state. Forming a good relationship with an electrician could be the difference between losing power for days and getting power turned back on within a couple of hours.
A home remodel is a very costly venture. Homeowners are always looking for ways to add value to their home. Renovating is a great way to update an area of your home and add value to your biggest investment, your house, If your existing electrical panel is full of circuit breakers, then it may be time to upgrade to a bigger panel. If your electrical panel still using fuses, then it may be time to upgrade to a bigger panel. If you are adding an addition or doing a major remodel, then you should also considering updating the electrical service to adequately service the new areas of your home.

profile:
Weenen Electric Inc. was established in 1986. David Weenen is the principal and is a licensed master electrician with 21 years of experience as an electrical contractor. He also has many more years of experience in the general contracting field.

Our roots are in the residential sector. David Weenen started his business by performing renovations in lovely, old Victorian homes in Cabbagetown. Fishing and rewiring homes is actually our prime business.

Thanks to our principal's construction background, we are 'head and shoulders' above the competition - when it comes to mitigating damages sustained to your existing wall surfaces when rewiring old knob and tube homes up to present day standards.

Potlights, sconces, jaccuzzi's, hot tubs, and in-floor radiant heating are just a few of the items we do each and everyday!

A typical residential electrical installation would include everything from replacing receptacles through to and including a complete rewire of your home. Whether it’s a newly built apartment, or a beautiful 19th Century house, Weenen Electric Inc. can handle any residential electrical project you may be contemplating.

Some more luxurious items you may be considering that require electrical connections are potlights, under counter lighting, sconces, jaccuzzis, hot tubs, and in-floor radiant heating, the installation of control systems for a pool or spa, home theatres data wiring etc. As well as re-wiring, we also do ‘pre-wiring’ for new construction projects and have expertise with low voltage systems involving voice, VOIP, data, and video wiring systems.

Our electricians are fully qualified, licensed, and have many many years of combined experience.

The most important service we can provide to you, is our 24 hour emergency service. We are located downtown and therefore can respond to your request in a timely fashion.

LK ELECTRIC - THREE GENERATIONS STRONG!! 

With vast knowledge of trouble shooting, we quickly identify and repair your problems with prompt service and reasonable pricing. LK Electric established itself in the GTA as an electrical trouble-shooter company. We identify and resolve home/office/store electrical problems in the fuses or breakers as well as installing lighting or hot water tanks. 

With all the new appliances and technical devices we now have in our homes an electric service upgrade is often recommended or required to increase the capacity of the existing electrical service. This is one of our areas of expertise.

profile:
T.W. Electrical Services Ltd is a full service Electrical Contractor in the GTA, offering an array of top quality electrical services for residential, commercial, and industrial clients.

Frank Tobin and Tom Wilson are fully licensed, highly skilled electricians who take the time to understand your needs, with an appreciation that everyone's installation, service, and repair requirements are unique.

Frank and Tom treat every client with respect, delivering exceptional service at every opportunity. They recognize that your home or business is your castle and pride, and as such, they carry out every electrical job knowing that the protection of your property comes first and foremost.

Not only are Frank and Tom reliable, fair, honest, organized, hard-working, and committed to you, the client, they are also smoke free, tidy, clean, and can ultimately provide you with peace of mind and a job well done. Frank and Tom are dedicated to quickly and efficiently completing your job with minimal electrical service downtime, without compromising on service or quality.

Knowledgeable and up-to-date regarding amendments to the electrical safety code, Frank and Tom will protect your home or business by providing in-depth electrical inspections on your electrical systems, thoroughly reviewing the challenges inherent in the work, and providing fair quotations that are based on a complete understanding of the job.

With over 25 years of experience as electricians between them, Frank, who hails from Ireland, and Tom, from England, worked as lead electricians on small, medium, and large sites in both Europe and Canada before their aspirations led them to join forces and open an electrical contracting business of their own in Toronto.

Frank Tobin, Master Electrician, has excelled as lead electrician in Ireland and Toronto in residential, commercial, and industrial settings, most notably as a contractor for companies in the solar panel, transportation, pharmaceutical, financial, security systems, and property development industries. Frank also recently completed emergency rescue and fire safety training at Seneca College, offering clients even more peace of mind.

​Tom Wilson has excelled as lead electrician in the United Kingdom and Toronto in residential, commercial, and industrial settings, most notably as a contractor for companies in the solar panel, food manufacturing, transportation, entertainment technology, health care, and property development industries.  

Clients respect Frank and Tom for their promptness, pleasant, professional, and trustworthy personalities, commitment to job quality and site safety, and strong work-ethic. As owner-operators, Frank and Tom recognize that their business depends on the satisfaction of every one of their clients.
